genresAdvancedInfo.name: classical contralto
genresAdvancedInfo.description: Classical contralto is a type of female singing voice that is low and rich in tone. It is often associated with dramatic and melancholic music, and is characterized by its deep and powerful resonance. Contralto singers are able to convey a wide range of emotions through their singing, and are often considered to be some of the most talented and expressive performers in the classical music world.
